Go on. hit it! Go!

20
00:02:30.820 --> 00:02:33.281
<i>One evening as the sun went down</i>

21
00:02:33.532 --> 00:02:35.909
<i>And the jungle fire was burning</i>

22
00:02:36.243 --> 00:02:38.578
<i>Down the track came a hobo hikin'</i>

23
00:02:38.787 --> 00:02:41.248
<i>And he said. boys. I'm not turning</i>

24
00:02:41.498 --> 00:02:44.251
<i>I'm headed for a land
that's far away</i>

25
00:02:44.584 --> 00:02:46.753
<i>Beside the crystal fountains</i>

26
00:02:47.087 --> 00:02:51.842
<i>So come with me. we'll go and see
the big rock candy mountains</i>

27
00:02:52.175 --> 00:02:54.594
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

28
00:02:54.845 --> 00:02:57.264
<i>There's a land
that's fair and bright</i>

29
00:02:57.514 --> 00:02:59.766
<i>Where the handouts grow on bushes</i>

30
00:03:00.016 --> 00:03:02.602
<i>And you sleep out every night</i>

31
00:03:02.769 --> 00:03:05.188
<i>Where the boxcars all are empty</i>

32
00:03:05.438 --> 00:03:07.107
<i>And the sun shines every day</i>

33
00:03:07.274 --> 00:03:10.610
<i>On the birds and the bees
and the cigarette trees</i>

34
00:03:10.861 --> 00:03:12.946
<i>The lemonade springs
where the bluebird sings</i>

35
00:03:13.113 --> 00:03:16.783
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

36
00:03:16.950 --> 00:03:19.286
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

37
00:03:19.619 --> 00:03:21.872
<i>All the cops have wooden legs</i>

38
00:03:22.205 --> 00:03:24.624
<i>And the bulldogs
all have rubber teeth</i>

39
00:03:24.875 --> 00:03:27.210
<i>And the hens lay soft-boiled eggs</i>

40
00:03:27.377 --> 00:03:29.713
<i>The farmers' trees
are full of fruit</i>

41
00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:32.215
<i>And the barns are full of hay</i>

42
00:03:32.382 --> 00:03:34.634
<i>Oh. I'm bound to go
where there ain't no snow</i>

43
00:03:34.801 --> 00:03:37.137
<i>Where the rain don't fall.
the wind don't blow</i>

44
00:03:37.304 --> 00:03:40.891
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

45
00:03:41.057 --> 00:03:43.476
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

46
00:03:43.810 --> 00:03:45.729
<i>You never change your socks</i>

47
00:03:46.062 --> 00:03:48.398
<i>And the little streams of alcohol</i>

48
00:03:48.565 --> 00:03:50.734
<i>Come a-trickling down the rocks</i>

49
00:03:51.067 --> 00:03:53.236
<i>The brakemen have to tip their hats</i>

50
00:03:53.486 --> 00:03:55.655
<i>And the railroad bulls are blind</i>

51
00:03:55.906 --> 00:03:58.241
<i>There's a lake of stew
and of whiskey. too</i>

52
00:03:58.575 --> 00:04:00.660
<i>You can paddle all around 'em
in a big canoe</i>

53
00:04:00.994 --> 00:04:04.748
<i>In the big rock
candy mountains...</i>

54
00:04:07.334 --> 00:04:09.336
<i>The jails are made of tin</i>

55
00:04:09.503 --> 00:04:11.588
<i>And you can walk right out again</i>

56
00:04:11.838 --> 00:04:14.257
<i>As soon as you are in</i>

57
00:04:14.508 --> 00:04:16.510
<i>There ain't no
short-handle shovels</i>

58
00:04:16.843 --> 00:04:19.012
<i>No axes. saws or picks</i>

59
00:04:19.262 --> 00:04:21.598
<i>I'm a-goin' to stay
where you sleep all day</i>

60
00:04:21.932 --> 00:04:23.850
<i>Where they hung the jerk
that invented work</i>

61
00:04:24.017 --> 00:04:28.021
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

62
00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:35.946
<i>I'll see you all this comin' fall</i>

63
00:04:36.154 --> 00:04:40.158
<i>In the big rock candy mountains</i>

64
00:05:16.152 --> 00:05:17.404
Say.

65
00:05:17.654 --> 00:05:21.157
any of you boys smithies?

66
00:05:22.325 --> 00:05:25.829
Or if not smithies.
trained in the metallurgic arts.

67
00:05:26.204 --> 00:05:30.959
before circumstances forced you
into a life of wanderin'?

68
00:05:40.177 --> 00:05:43.096
Jesus! Can't I count on you people?

69
00:05:43.263 --> 00:05:45.015
Sorry. Everett.

70
00:05:45.265 --> 00:05:50.020
Well. all right.
If we take off through that bayou...

71
00:05:50.270 --> 00:05:51.605
Wait a minute!

72
00:05:51.855 --> 00:05:54.357
Who elected you leader
of this outfit?

73
00:05:54.608 --> 00:05:58.528
I figured it should be the one with
the capacity for abstract thought.

74
00:05:58.695 --> 00:06:01.865
but if that ain't the consensus.
then hell. let's vote.

75
00:06:02.032 --> 00:06:04.534
Suits me!
I'm votin' for yours truly.

76
00:06:04.868 --> 00:06:08.705
Well. I'm votin'
for yours truly. too.

77
00:06:12.042 --> 00:06:15.462
OK. I'm with you fellas.

78
00:06:39.569 --> 00:06:42.489
Mind if we join you. old-timer?

79
00:06:42.739 --> 00:06:47.911
Join me. m'son. Join me.

80
00:06:49.079 --> 00:06:52.332
You work
for the railroad. grandpa?

81
00:06:52.582 --> 00:06:54.835
I work for no man.

82
00:06:55.001 --> 00:06:59.089
- Got a name. do you?
- I have no name.

83
00:06:59.422 --> 00:07:03.593
That may be why you had difficulty
finding gainful employment.

84
00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:06.680
Y'see. in the mart
of competitive commerce...

85
00:07:07.013 --> 00:07:08.765
You seek a great fortune.

86
00:07:09.015 --> 00:07:11.518
you three who are now in chains.

87
00:07:11.768 --> 00:07:14.437
You will find a fortune.

88
00:07:14.688 --> 00:07:18.024
though it will not be
the fortune you seek.

89
00:07:18.275 --> 00:07:20.443
But first...

90
00:07:20.694 --> 00:07:26.533
first you must travel
a long and difficult road.

91
00:07:26.783 --> 00:07:31.538
a road fraught with peril. mm-hmm.

92
00:07:31.705 --> 00:07:34.875
You shall see things...

93
00:07:35.041 --> 00:07:37.210
wonderful to tell.

94
00:07:37.460 --> 00:07:40.881
You shall see a... a cow...

95
00:07:41.214 --> 00:07:45.719
on the roof of a cotton house. ha.

96
00:07:45.969 --> 00:07:50.307
And. oh. so many startlements.

97
00:07:50.473 --> 00:07:53.643
I cannot tell you how long
this road shall be.

98
00:07:53.810 --> 00:07:57.063
but fear not the obstacles
in your path.

99
00:07:57.397 --> 00:07:58.648
for fate has...

100
00:07:58.899 --> 00:08:02.068
vouchsafed your reward.

101
00:08:02.235 --> 00:08:05.071
Though the road may wind.

102
00:08:05.405 --> 00:08:07.908
yea. your hearts grow weary.

103
00:08:08.074 --> 00:08:10.911
still shall ye follow them.

104
00:08:11.161 --> 00:08:15.999
even unto your salvation.

105
00:08:27.844 --> 00:08:31.681
No. the treasure's
still there. believe me.

106
00:08:31.848 --> 00:08:34.267
But how'd he know about it?

107
00:08:34.518 --> 00:08:38.438
I don't know. Delmar. The blind
reputedly possess sensitivities

108
00:08:38.688 --> 00:08:40.524
compensating for lack of sight.

109
00:08:40.774 --> 00:08:43.443
to the point of developing
psychic powers.

110
00:08:43.777 --> 00:08:47.197
Clearly. seeing the future
falls into that category.

111
00:08:47.447 --> 00:08:51.451
It's not so surprising. then.
that one lacking earthly vision...

112
00:08:51.701 --> 00:08:54.704
He said we wouldn't get
the treasure we seek.

113
00:08:54.955 --> 00:08:56.623
on account of our obstacles.

114
00:08:56.790 --> 00:08:59.626
What the hell
does an ignorant old man know?

115
00:08:59.793 --> 00:09:02.629
Jesus. Pete. I told you
I buried it myself.

116
00:09:02.879 --> 00:09:04.965
If your cousin still has this farm

117
00:09:05.131 --> 00:09:08.510
and shoein' impedimenta
to restore liberty of movement...

118
00:09:09.970 --> 00:09:11.721
Hold it right there!

119
00:09:11.888 --> 00:09:15.684
You men from the bank?

120
00:09:15.892 --> 00:09:17.477
You Wash's boy?

121
00:09:17.644 --> 00:09:21.398
Yes. sir. Daddy told me to shoot
who's ever from the bank.

122
00:09:21.648 --> 00:09:24.150
We ain't from the bank. young fella.

123
00:09:24.317 --> 00:09:27.737
Yes. sir. I'm supposed to shoot folks
servin' papers.

124
00:09:28.071 --> 00:09:31.616
- We ain't got no papers. neither.
- I nicked the census man.

125
00:09:31.825 --> 00:09:33.994
Now. there's a good boy.

126
00:09:34.327 --> 00:09:36.413
Is... is your daddy about?

127
00:09:48.925 --> 00:09:50.594
Hello. Pete.

128
00:09:50.927 --> 00:09:52.929
Who are your friends?

129
00:09:53.221 --> 00:09:56.016
Pleased to make
your acquaintance. Mr Hogwallop.

130
00:09:56.266 --> 00:10:01.408
- My name's Ulysses Everett McGill...
- I'm Delmar O'Donnel.

131
00:10:01.438 --> 00:10:03.356
How you been. Wash?

132
00:10:03.523 --> 00:10:06.443
Been what. 12. 13 years?

133
00:10:09.362 --> 00:10:11.448
Yeah...

134
00:10:11.781 --> 00:10:15.410
I expect you want
them chains knocked off.

135
00:10:15.619 --> 00:10:18.371
They foreclosed
on cousin Bishop.

136
00:10:18.622 --> 00:10:21.500
He hanged hisself a year come May.

137
00:10:21.666 --> 00:10:23.585
And Uncle Radcliffe?

138
00:10:23.752 --> 00:10:26.046
The anthrax
took most of his cows.

139
00:10:26.296 --> 00:10:27.923
The rest don't milk.

140
00:10:28.131 --> 00:10:30.967
He lost a boy to mumps.

141
00:10:31.301 --> 00:10:35.055
Where's Cora. Cousin Wash?

142
00:10:37.724 --> 00:10:41.728
Couldn't say.

143
00:10:41.811 --> 00:10:48.068
Mrs Hogwallop up and R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

144
00:10:48.401 --> 00:10:51.404
She must have been
lookin' for answers.

145
00:10:51.738 --> 00:10:54.908
Possibly. Good riddance.
as far as I'm concerned.

146
00:10:55.158 --> 00:10:58.078
I do miss
her cooking. though.

147
00:10:58.245 --> 00:11:02.165
- This stew's awful good.
- Think so?

148
00:11:02.415 --> 00:11:05.085
I slaughtered this horse
last Tuesday.

149
00:11:05.293 --> 00:11:09.923
I'm afraid
she's startin' to turn.

150
00:11:13.426 --> 00:11:16.179
<i>You are my sunshine</i>

151
00:11:16.429 --> 00:11:19.349
<i>My only sunshine</i>

152
00:11:19.516 --> 00:11:21.351
<i>You make me happy</i>

153
00:11:21.518 --> 00:11:23.937
<i>When skies are grey</i>

154
00:11:24.104 --> 00:11:26.606
<i>You'll never know. dear</i>

155
00:11:26.940 --> 00:11:29.442
<i>How much I love you</i>

156
00:11:29.776 --> 00:11:34.447
<i>Please don't take
my sunshine away</i>

157
00:11:34.698 --> 00:11:39.786
<i>That winds up the Pass The
Biscuits Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour.</i>

158
00:11:39.953 --> 00:11:41.371
<i>This is Pappy O'Daniel</i>

159
00:11:41.621 --> 00:11:44.457
<i>hopin' you been enjoyin'
that old-timey music.</i>

160
00:11:44.708 --> 00:11:46.626
<i>And remember.</i>

161
00:11:46.877 --> 00:11:50.297
<i>when you're fixing to
bake a mess of biscuits.</i>

162
00:11:50.630 --> 00:11:52.382
<i>use cool. clear water</i>

163
00:11:52.632 --> 00:11:56.803
<i>and good. pure.
Pappy O'Daniel flour.</i>

164
00:11:57.053 --> 00:12:02.309
Well. guess I'll be turnin' in.
Say. uh. cousin Wash.

165
00:12:02.475 --> 00:12:04.728
I suppose it'd be
the acme of foolishness

166
00:12:04.895 --> 00:12:06.813
to ask if you had a hair net.

167
00:12:07.063 --> 00:12:09.816
We got a bunch in yon bureau.

168
00:12:09.983 --> 00:12:12.402
Mrs Hogwallop's. matter of fact.

169
00:12:12.736 --> 00:12:17.240
Help yourself.
I won't be needing 'em.

170
00:12:17.407 --> 00:12:19.075
<i>You are my sunshine</i>

171
00:12:19.326 --> 00:12:22.662
<i>My only sunshine</i>

172
00:12:22.913 --> 00:12:25.332
<i>You make me happy</i>

173
00:12:25.582 --> 00:12:27.083
<i>When skies are grey...</i>

174
00:12:27.334 --> 00:12:29.503
All right. boys!

175
00:12:31.004 --> 00:12:32.672
How's my hair?

176
00:12:32.923 --> 00:12:37.260
It's the authorities!
We got you surrounded.

177
00:12:37.511 --> 00:12:39.429
Damn. we're in a tight spot.

178
00:12:39.596 --> 00:12:42.682
Just come on out
and grab at air!

179
00:12:42.849 --> 00:12:45.352
And don't try nothin' fancy.

180
00:12:45.602 --> 00:12:48.104
Your situation
is pretty nigh hopeless.

181
00:12:48.271 --> 00:12:52.025
- Damn! We're in a tight spot!
- What in the Sam Hill...?

182
00:12:52.275 --> 00:12:54.027
Pete's cousin turned us in.

183
00:12:54.361 --> 00:12:55.362
What the hell you sayin'?!

184
00:12:55.695 --> 00:12:57.447
Wash is kin!

185
00:12:57.697 --> 00:12:58.782
Sorry. Pete!

186
00:12:59.115 --> 00:13:02.702
I know we're kin.
but they got this depression on.

187
00:13:02.869 --> 00:13:04.621
I got to do for me and mine.

188
00:13:04.871 --> 00:13:09.125
I'm gonna kill you.
Judas Iscariot Hogwallop!

189
00:13:09.459 --> 00:13:13.713
You miserable.
horse-eatin' son of a...

190
00:13:13.797 --> 00:13:15.632
Damn! We're in a tight spot!

191
00:13:15.882 --> 00:13:17.467
Damn his eyes!

192
00:13:17.717 --> 00:13:21.555
Pa always said.
"Never trust a Hogwallop".

193
00:13:21.721 --> 00:13:24.224
Come and get us. coppers!

194
00:13:25.892 --> 00:13:29.396
You leave us no choice
but to smoke you out.

195
00:13:29.646 --> 00:13:31.314
We're in a tight spot.

196
00:13:31.648 --> 00:13:32.566
Light her up!

197
00:13:32.899 --> 00:13:36.152
Hold up!
Ain't you ever heard of negotiatin'?

198
00:13:36.486 --> 00:13:38.738
We could talk this thing out.
I hate fire!

199
00:13:39.072 --> 00:13:43.743
You lousy. yella-bellied...
Pete. we need one voice.

200
00:13:44.077 --> 00:13:47.581
Careful with that fire!

201
00:13:48.331 --> 00:13:50.250
Light the loft. son.

202
00:13:50.417 --> 00:13:52.752
Aah! I hate fire!

203
00:13:52.919 --> 00:13:57.090
Gapped-toothed. carpetbaggin'.
motherless spawn of hell!

204
00:13:57.340 --> 00:14:00.093
Step back. Damn it. Look out.

205
00:14:00.427 --> 00:14:02.095
Holy Saint Christopher!

206
00:14:02.345 --> 00:14:04.848
Get away from that.
she's liquid fire!

207
00:14:06.516 --> 00:14:10.687
Take cover. boys! It ain't popcorn!

208
00:14:20.447 --> 00:14:23.283
Scatter. boys!

209
00:14:24.534 --> 00:14:27.370
God damn it!

210
00:14:30.457 --> 00:14:31.708
Get in. boys!

211
00:14:32.042 --> 00:14:34.461
I'm gonna R-U-N-N-O-F-T!

212
00:14:34.628 --> 00:14:38.381
Come on. boys. come on! Come on!

213
00:14:38.715 --> 00:14:42.802
What are you doing here? You ought
to be in bed. clump snatcher.

214
00:14:43.053 --> 00:14:46.139
You ain't the boss of me!

215
00:14:52.562 --> 00:14:56.233
You candy-butted.
car-thievin' sos-and-sos!

216
00:14:56.566 --> 00:14:58.485
I curse your name!

217
00:14:58.818 --> 00:15:01.571
Go back home and mind your pa!

218
00:15:05.325 --> 00:15:08.829
What's the damn problem?

219
00:15:09.579 --> 00:15:12.999
I can get the part from Bristol
in two weeks. Your pomade.

220
00:15:13.333 --> 00:15:16.169
Two weeks?
That don't do me no good.

221
00:15:16.336 --> 00:15:18.839
Nearest Ford auto man's Bristol.

222
00:15:19.089 --> 00:15:22.425
Hold on. I don't want this pomade.
I want Dapper Dan.

223
00:15:22.676 --> 00:15:25.512
I don't carry Dapper Dan.
I carry Fop.

224
00:15:25.846 --> 00:15:29.266
I don't want Fop. god damn it!
I'm a Dapper Dan man!

225
00:15:29.516 --> 00:15:32.102
Watch your language.
this is a public market.

226
00:15:32.435 --> 00:15:36.773
Now. if you want Dapper Dan.
I can have it in a coupla weeks.

227
00:15:37.023 --> 00:15:40.527
Ain't this a geographical oddity!
Two weeks from everywhere.

228
00:15:40.777 --> 00:15:42.612
Forget it.

229
00:15:42.946 --> 00:15:46.700
Just a dozen hair nets.

230
00:15:46.867 --> 00:15:49.619
Well. didn't look
like a one-horse town.

231
00:15:49.786 --> 00:15:52.205
but try finding
a decent hair jelly.

232
00:15:52.455 --> 00:15:56.626
- Gopher. Everett?
- No transmission belt for two weeks.

233
00:15:56.793 --> 00:15:59.546
Huh? They dam that river on the 21st.

234
00:15:59.713 --> 00:16:02.132
- Today is the 17th.
- Don't I know it.

235
00:16:02.299 --> 00:16:04.968
We got but four days
to get to that treasure.

236
00:16:05.218 --> 00:16:08.054
After that. it'll be
at the bottom of a lake.

237
00:16:08.305 --> 00:16:10.140
We won't make it walkin'.

238
00:16:10.390 --> 00:16:12.475
- Right...
- Gopher?

239
00:16:12.642 --> 00:16:14.978
But the old tactician's got a plan.

240
00:16:15.228 --> 00:16:19.149
For the transportation.
not keeping my coiffure in order.

241
00:16:19.316 --> 00:16:22.485
How's this a plan?
How we gonna get a car?

242
00:16:22.652 --> 00:16:27.157
Sell that. I figure you can only have
painful association for Wash.

243
00:16:27.490 --> 00:16:31.912
"To Washington Bartholomew Hogwallop.

244
00:16:32.162 --> 00:16:33.580
from his lovin' Cora".

245
00:16:33.914 --> 00:16:39.252
- "Amor fidel... is".
- It was in his bureau.

246
00:16:39.586 --> 00:16:42.756
I reckon it'll fetch us enough
for a good auto voiture

247
00:16:43.006 --> 00:16:44.758
and a little leftover besides.

248
00:16:45.091 --> 00:16:47.511
Whoo! You got light fingers. Everett.

249
00:16:47.761 --> 00:16:51.431
- Gopher?
- You miserable little snake.

250
00:16:51.765 --> 00:16:53.517
You stole from my kin!

251
00:16:53.767 --> 00:16:56.269
Who was fixin' to betray us.

252
00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:58.522
You didn't know that at the time.

253
00:16:58.772 --> 00:17:00.857
So I borrowed it till I did know.

254
00:17:01.024 --> 00:17:03.026
That don't make no sense!

255
00:17:03.193 --> 00:17:06.029
A fool seeks logic
in the chambers of the heart.

256
00:17:06.363 --> 00:17:10.867
What the hell is that singing?

257
00:17:12.285 --> 00:17:17.958
Appears to be some kind
of a... congregation.

258
00:17:18.124 --> 00:17:21.795
Care for some gopher?

259
00:17:23.630 --> 00:17:25.465
No. thank you. Delmar.

260
00:17:25.632 --> 00:17:28.552
A third of a gopher'd
only arouse my appetite

261
00:17:28.885 --> 00:17:31.137
without beddin' her back down.

262
00:17:31.388 --> 00:17:33.640
Oh. you can have the whole thing.

263
00:17:33.974 --> 00:17:36.810
Me and Pete already had one.

264
00:17:37.143 --> 00:17:45.902
We ran across
a whole... gopher... village.

265
00:17:48.822 --> 00:17:52.242
<i>O brothers. let's go down</i>

266
00:17:52.576 --> 00:17:56.163
<i>Let's go down. come on down</i>

267
00:17:56.538 --> 00:17:59.833
<i>Come on. brothers. let's go down</i>

268
00:18:00.167 --> 00:18:04.212
<i>Down in the river to pray</i>

269
00:18:04.504 --> 00:18:08.258
<i>As I went down
in the river to pray</i>

270
00:18:08.508 --> 00:18:11.386
<i>Studyin' about that good old way</i>

271
00:18:11.761 --> 00:18:15.098
<i>And who shall wear
the starry crown</i>

272
00:18:15.307 --> 00:18:19.686
<i>Good Lord. show me the way</i>

273
00:18:19.853 --> 00:18:23.440
<i>O fathers. let's go down</i>

274
00:18:23.690 --> 00:18:27.277
<i>Let's go down. come on down</i>

275
00:18:27.444 --> 00:18:30.822
<i>O fathers. let's go down</i>

276
00:18:31.114 --> 00:18:35.285
<i>Down in the river to pray</i>

277
00:18:35.619 --> 00:18:39.456
<i>As I went down
in the river to pray</i>

278
00:18:39.664 --> 00:18:42.792
<i>Studying about that good old way</i>

279
00:18:43.043 --> 00:18:46.379
<i>And who shall wear
the robe and crown</i>

280
00:18:46.588 --> 00:18:51.218
<i>Good lord. show me the way</i>

281
00:18:51.551 --> 00:18:54.930
<i>O mothers. let's go down</i>

282
00:18:55.138 --> 00:18:58.433
<i>Come on down.
don't you wanna go down?</i>

283
00:18:58.642 --> 00:19:02.395
<i>Come on. mothers.
let's go down...</i>

284
00:19:02.604 --> 00:19:05.732
Well. I guess hard times
flush the chumps.

285
00:19:05.982 --> 00:19:08.068
Everybody's lookin' for answers.

286
00:19:11.988 --> 00:19:13.698
Where the hell's he going?

287
00:19:13.949 --> 00:19:17.869
The Father. the Son
and the Holy Ghost.

288
00:19:18.119 --> 00:19:22.040
<i>Good Lord. show me the way</i>

289
00:19:22.249 --> 00:19:26.670
<i>O sinners. let's go down...</i>

290
00:19:27.003 --> 00:19:29.339
Well. I'll be a son of a bitch.

291
00:19:29.506 --> 00:19:31.508
Delmar's been saved.

292
00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:34.761
Well. that's it. boys.
I been redeemed.

293
00:19:34.928 --> 00:19:39.182
The preacher done washed away
all my sins and transgressions.

294
00:19:39.432 --> 00:19:42.227
It's the straight and narrow
from here on out.

295
00:19:42.519 --> 00:19:45.021
And heaven everlasting's
my reward.

296
00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:48.483
Delmar. what are you on about?
We got bigger fish to fry.

297
00:19:48.692 --> 00:19:51.695
The preacher said
all my sins is washed away.

298
00:19:51.945 --> 00:19:54.948
including that Piggly Wiggly
I knocked over in Yazoo.

299
00:19:55.198 --> 00:19:57.284
You said you was innocent of that.

300
00:19:57.492 --> 00:19:59.786
Well. I was lyin'.

301
00:19:59.953 --> 00:20:03.748
And the preacher said that
that sin's been washed away. too.

302
00:20:03.957 --> 00:20:07.252
Neither God nor man's
got nothin' on me now.

303
00:20:07.544 --> 00:20:12.465
Come on in. boys.
The water is fine.

304
00:20:18.388 --> 00:20:21.224
Come on. boy.
There. boy. Good doggy.

305
00:20:23.727 --> 00:20:27.606
All right. boys. we got the scent.

306
00:20:30.192 --> 00:20:33.987
- The preacher said it absolved us.
- For Him. not for the law.

307
00:20:34.154 --> 00:20:36.907
I gave you credit for
more brains than Delmar.

308
00:20:37.115 --> 00:20:41.161
- But witnesses seen us redeemed.
- That's not the issue. Delmar.

309
00:20:41.495 --> 00:20:44.664
Even square with the Lord.
Mississippi's hard-nosed.

310
00:20:44.915 --> 00:20:48.335
You shoulda joined us. Everett.
It couldn'a hurt none.

311
00:20:48.585 --> 00:20:51.963
Hell. it woulda washed away
the stink of that pomade.

312
00:20:52.339 --> 00:20:55.884
Joining you fools in superstition?
Thank you. anyway.

313
00:20:56.134 --> 00:21:01.473
And I like the smell of my hair.
the pleasin' odour's half the point.

314
00:21:01.681 --> 00:21:03.683
Baptism!

315
00:21:03.850 --> 00:21:06.186
You two are
dumber than a bag of hammers.

316
00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:08.396
You're my cross to bear.

317
00:21:08.605 --> 00:21:13.485
Pull over. Everett. Let's give
that coloured boy a lift.

318
00:21:19.449 --> 00:21:21.827
You folks going past Tishomingo?

319
00:21:22.035 --> 00:21:24.955
Sure. hop in.

320
00:21:31.962 --> 00:21:34.214
How you doin'. son? Name's Everett.

321
00:21:34.548 --> 00:21:37.843
These two soggy sons of bitches
are Pete and Delmar.

322
00:21:38.218 --> 00:21:41.972
Keep your fingers away from Pete's
mouth. he ain't eaten for 13 years.

323
00:21:42.138 --> 00:21:44.474
'cept prison food and greasy horse.

324
00:21:44.766 --> 00:21:48.645
Thanks for the lift. sir.
My name's Tommy. Tommy Johnson.

325
00:21:48.937 --> 00:21:50.814
How you doin'. Tommy?

326
00:21:51.022 --> 00:21:54.067
Say. I haven't seen a house
out here for miles.

327
00:21:54.317 --> 00:21:56.820
Why are you
out in the middle of nowhere?

328
00:21:57.070 --> 00:21:59.739
I had to be at that crossroads
last midnight.

329
00:22:00.073 --> 00:22:01.950
Sell my soul to the devil.

330
00:22:02.159 --> 00:22:04.703
Ain't it a small world.
spiritually speakin'?

331
00:22:04.911 --> 00:22:09.082
Pete and Delmar just been saved.
I'm the only one still unaffiliated.

332
00:22:09.332 --> 00:22:11.418
It's no laughin' matter.

333
00:22:11.751 --> 00:22:13.503
What'd the devil give you for it?

334
00:22:13.753 --> 00:22:17.215
Well. he taught me to play
this here guitar real good.

335
00:22:17.424 --> 00:22:21.636
Oh. son. for that you traded
your everlasting soul?

336
00:22:22.012 --> 00:22:23.471
Well. I wasn't usin' it.

337
00:22:23.680 --> 00:22:27.851
I've always wondered.
what's the devil look like?

338
00:22:28.018 --> 00:22:31.605
Well. there are all manner
of lesser imps and demons.

339
00:22:31.813 --> 00:22:35.442
but Satan hisself is red and scaly
with a bifurcated tail.

340
00:22:35.775 --> 00:22:39.196
- and he carries a hayfork.
- Oh. no. No. sir.

341
00:22:39.362 --> 00:22:42.866
He's white.
As white as you folks.

342
00:22:43.033 --> 00:22:45.952
With empty eyes
and a big. hollow voice.

343
00:22:46.203 --> 00:22:49.956
He travelled around
with a mean old hound. that's right.

344
00:22:50.123 --> 00:22:52.125
He told you to go to Tishomingo?

345
00:22:52.292 --> 00:22:55.128
Well. no. sir.
Why. that was my idea.

346
00:22:55.462 --> 00:22:57.214
I heard there's a man there.

347
00:22:57.547 --> 00:22:59.799
pays folks money
to sing into his can.

348
00:23:00.133 --> 00:23:03.970
They say he pays extra
if'n you play real good.

349
00:23:04.221 --> 00:23:06.056
Tishomingo. huh?

350
00:23:06.306 --> 00:23:07.891
How much he pay?

351
00:23:24.324 --> 00:23:28.995
All right. boys. follow my lead.

352
00:23:33.083 --> 00:23:35.502
Hello?

353
00:23:35.836 --> 00:23:40.423
- Who's the honcho here?
- I am. Who are you?

354
00:23:40.590 --> 00:23:45.095
Well. sir. I'm Jordan Rivers.
and these are the Soggy Bottom Boys.

355
00:23:45.262 --> 00:23:47.264
out of Cottonillia. Mississippi.

356
00:23:47.514 --> 00:23:49.850
Songs of salvation to salve the soul.

357
00:23:50.183 --> 00:23:53.937
Uh. we hear that you pay good money
to sing into a can.

358
00:23:54.187 --> 00:23:57.524
Well. that all depends.
You boys do Negro songs?

359
00:23:57.691 --> 00:24:02.612
Um... Well. uh. sir. we are Negroes.

360
00:24:02.779 --> 00:24:06.867
All except for our accomp... accomp...
the fella that plays the guitar.

361
00:24:07.117 --> 00:24:09.286
Yeah. well.
I don't record Negro songs.

362
00:24:09.619 --> 00:24:12.956
No. I'm lookin' for
some old-timey material.

363
00:24:13.206 --> 00:24:15.208
People can't seem to get enough

364
00:24:15.458 --> 00:24:18.879
since we started broadcasting it
on the Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour.

365
00:24:19.212 --> 00:24:21.381
so thank you for stopping by. but...

366
00:24:21.715 --> 00:24:26.469
Sir. the Soggy Bottom Boys have been
steeped in old-timey material.

367
00:24:26.720 --> 00:24:29.389
- Heck. we're silly with it.
- That's right.

368
00:24:29.723 --> 00:24:31.725
Right. We ain't really Negroes.

369
00:24:31.975 --> 00:24:34.060
All except for our accompanist.

370
00:24:36.730 --> 00:24:40.984
<i>I am a man</i>

371
00:24:41.151 --> 00:24:43.987
<i>Of constant sorrow</i>

372
00:24:44.237 --> 00:24:50.243
<i>I've seen trouble all my days</i>

373
00:24:50.494 --> 00:24:54.831
<i>I bid farewell</i>

374
00:24:55.165 --> 00:24:57.667
<i>To old Kentucky</i>

375
00:24:58.001 --> 00:25:00.253
<i>The place where I</i>

376
00:25:00.504 --> 00:25:03.173
<i>Was born and raised</i>

377
00:25:03.423 --> 00:25:06.176
<i>The place where he</i>

378
00:25:06.510 --> 00:25:09.846
<i>Was born and raised</i>

379
00:25:10.096 --> 00:25:14.434
<i>For six long years</i>

380
00:25:14.768 --> 00:25:17.270
<i>I've been in trouble</i>

381
00:25:17.604 --> 00:25:20.190
<i>No pleasure here</i>

382
00:25:20.524 --> 00:25:23.860
<i>On Earth I found</i>

383
00:25:24.027 --> 00:25:28.281
<i>For in this world</i>

384
00:25:28.532 --> 00:25:30.700
<i>I'm bound to ramble</i>

385
00:25:30.951 --> 00:25:33.954
<i>I have no friends</i>

386
00:25:34.120 --> 00:25:36.790
<i>To help me now</i>

387
00:25:37.040 --> 00:25:39.543
<i>He has no friends</i>

388
00:25:39.876 --> 00:25:43.296
<i>To help him now</i>

389
00:25:43.630 --> 00:25:48.051
<i>Maybe your friends think</i>

390
00:25:48.301 --> 00:25:50.804
<i>I'm just a stranger</i>

391
00:25:51.137 --> 00:25:53.557
<i>My face you never</i>

392
00:25:53.890 --> 00:25:55.141
<i>Will see no more</i>

393
00:25:57.644 --> 00:26:02.399
<i>But there is one promise</i>

394
00:26:02.732 --> 00:26:04.734
<i>That is given</i>

395
00:26:04.901 --> 00:26:07.487
<i>I'll meet you on</i>

396
00:26:07.821 --> 00:26:10.323
<i>God's golden shore</i>

397
00:26:10.657 --> 00:26:13.243
<i>He'll meet you on</i>

398
00:26:13.493 --> 00:26:18.498
<i>God's golden shore</i>

399
00:26:19.833 --> 00:26:23.336
Whoo! Hot damn. son!
You did sell your soul to the devil!

400
00:26:25.172 --> 00:26:29.009
Boy. that was some mighty fine
a-pickin' and a-singin'.

401
00:26:29.176 --> 00:26:30.594
I'll tell you what.

402
00:26:30.760 --> 00:26:33.096
Ahem. You come on
in here. you...

403
00:26:33.263 --> 00:26:37.767
you sign these papers here.
I'm gonna give you $10 apiece.

404
00:26:38.101 --> 00:26:44.191
Uh. OK. sir. but Mert and...
Aloysious'll have to sign x's.

405
00:26:44.524 --> 00:26:48.528
- Only four of us can write.
- That'd be fine.

406
00:26:51.448 --> 00:26:54.784
Hey. mister. I don't mean
to tell tales out of school.

407
00:26:54.951 --> 00:26:58.788
but there's a fella in there'll pay
you $10 if you sing into his can.

408
00:26:59.122 --> 00:27:02.125
I'm not hear to make a record.
you dumb cracker.

409
00:27:02.375 --> 00:27:04.211
They broadcast me on the radio.

410
00:27:04.461 --> 00:27:07.380
That's Governor Menelaus
"Pappy" O'Daniel.

411
00:27:07.714 --> 00:27:11.718
He'd sure like it if you ate his
farina and voted him a second term.

412
00:27:12.052 --> 00:27:14.638
- Finest in Mississippi.
- In any state.

413
00:27:14.971 --> 00:27:17.140
Lord. yes. Every parish.

414
00:27:17.390 --> 00:27:20.227
Ain't you gonna
press the flesh. Pappy?

415
00:27:20.393 --> 00:27:23.647
I'll press your flesh.
you dim-witted son'bitch.

416
00:27:23.813 --> 00:27:27.734
Don't tell me how to court the
electorate. We ain't one-at-a-timin'.

417
00:27:27.984 --> 00:27:29.653
We're mass communicatin'!

418
00:27:29.903 --> 00:27:32.489
Oh. yes. that's a powerful new force.

419
00:27:32.739 --> 00:27:34.157
Shake a leg. Junior.

420
00:27:34.407 --> 00:27:36.743
Thank God your mammy died
givin' birth.

421
00:27:36.993 --> 00:27:38.578
she'd have died of shame.

422
00:27:38.745 --> 00:27:40.747
Well. hi there! How you doin'?

423
00:27:42.749 --> 00:27:48.338
<i>Hard time yearnin'
where you go</i>

424
00:27:48.588 --> 00:27:54.177
<i>Times is harder
than ever been before</i>

425
00:27:59.432 --> 00:28:02.519
<i>And the people are driftin'</i>

426
00:28:02.769 --> 00:28:05.272
<i>From door to door</i>

427
00:28:05.522 --> 00:28:06.940
<i>Can't find no heaven</i>

428
00:28:07.107 --> 00:28:10.443
<i>I don't care where they go</i>

429
00:28:21.121 --> 00:28:23.623
<i>Say you had money</i>

430
00:28:23.790 --> 00:28:26.293
<i>You better be sure</i>

431
00:28:26.543 --> 00:28:28.378
<i>These hard times will drive you</i>

432
00:28:28.628 --> 00:28:31.548
<i>From door to door</i>

433
00:28:43.310 --> 00:28:45.729
Let's bed down here for the night.

434
00:28:45.896 --> 00:28:49.566
Yeah. it stinks in that old barn.

435
00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:51.234
Suits me.

436
00:28:51.568 --> 00:28:57.407
Pretty soon it'll be nothin' but
featherbeds and silk sheets.

437
00:29:00.494 --> 00:29:02.245
A million dollars.

438
00:29:02.579 --> 00:29:04.498
Million point two.

439
00:29:04.748 --> 00:29:09.503
- 500.000 each.
- 400. Delmar.

440
00:29:09.669 --> 00:29:16.343
Pete. what are you gonna do
with your share of the treasure?

441
00:29:16.676 --> 00:29:19.179
Go out west somewhere.

442
00:29:19.346 --> 00:29:23.016
Open a fine restaurant.

443
00:29:23.099 --> 00:29:26.603
I'm gonna be the maitre d'.

444
00:29:26.770 --> 00:29:29.523
Greet all the swells.

445
00:29:29.689 --> 00:29:33.026
Go to work every day
in a bow tie.

446
00:29:33.276 --> 00:29:35.362
tuxedo.

447
00:29:35.529 --> 00:29:39.115
And all the staff
say "yes. sir" and...

448
00:29:39.282 --> 00:29:40.617
"no. sir"...

449
00:29:40.867 --> 00:29:44.287
and "in a jiffy. Pete".

450
00:29:44.621 --> 00:29:48.708
And all my meals for free.

451
00:29:51.628 --> 00:29:53.463
What about you. Delmar.

452
00:29:53.713 --> 00:29:56.883
what are you gonna do
with your share of that dough?

453
00:29:57.217 --> 00:30:00.887
I'm gonna visit them
foreclosin' son of a guns

454
00:30:01.054 --> 00:30:04.724
down at the Indianola
Savings and Loan.

455
00:30:04.975 --> 00:30:10.981
Slap that money on the barrel head
and buy back the family farm.

456
00:30:11.231 --> 00:30:15.819
You ain't no kind of man
if you ain't got land.

457
00:30:15.986 --> 00:30:17.904
What about you. Everett?

458
00:30:18.155 --> 00:30:21.908
What you have in mind
when you stole it in the first place?

459
00:30:22.242 --> 00:30:28.498
Ahem. I... didn't have no plan.

460
00:30:28.748 --> 00:30:31.668
Well. that hardly sounds like you.

461
00:30:31.918 --> 00:30:35.172
All right. boys!
It's the authorities!

462
00:30:35.422 --> 00:30:38.008
Your situation
is purty nigh hopeless!

463
00:30:38.175 --> 00:30:40.594
Damn. they found our car.

464
00:30:40.844 --> 00:30:43.930
We ain't got the time
and nary the inclination

465
00:30:44.264 --> 00:30:46.683
to chat with you boys any further.

466
00:30:46.933 --> 00:30:49.019
Damn. we got to skedaddle.

467
00:30:49.269 --> 00:30:53.190
I left my pomade in the car.
Maybe I can creep up.

468
00:30:53.523 --> 00:30:57.777
Don't be a fool. Everett.
We got to R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

469
00:30:58.111 --> 00:31:00.030
Where's Tommy?

470
00:31:00.197 --> 00:31:05.452
Already lit out.
scared out of his wits.

471
00:31:06.536 --> 00:31:09.456
Let's go!

472
00:31:09.706 --> 00:31:11.708
Well. hell. it ain't square one.

473
00:31:11.875 --> 00:31:15.962
Ain't no one gonna pick up three
filthy. unshaved hitchhikers.

474
00:31:16.296 --> 00:31:20.217
And one of them a know-it-all
who can't keep his trap shut.

475
00:31:20.467 --> 00:31:24.721
The rancour reflected in that remark
I won't dignify with comment.

476
00:31:25.055 --> 00:31:29.226
But I'll address your general
attitude of hopeless negativism.

477
00:31:29.392 --> 00:31:32.229
Consider the lilies
of the goddam field.

478
00:31:32.395 --> 00:31:35.482
Or. hell. look at Delmar
as your paradigm of hope.

479
00:31:35.649 --> 00:31:37.317
Yeah. Look at me.

480
00:31:37.567 --> 00:31:41.488
You may call it unreasoning optimism.
you may call it obtuse.

481
00:31:41.738 --> 00:31:44.908
but the plain and simple fact
is we got close to...

482
00:31:45.158 --> 00:31:47.744
three days before they...

483
00:31:52.582 --> 00:31:56.837
dam that river.

484
00:32:18.942 --> 00:32:22.779
Is this the road to Itta Bena?

485
00:32:22.863 --> 00:32:25.699
Uh... Itta Bena?

486
00:32:25.949 --> 00:32:30.287
Itta Bena?
Stay on this here road.

487
00:32:30.537 --> 00:32:33.874
That ain't right.
I was thinking of...

488
00:32:34.124 --> 00:32:36.459
- Take this road.
- Nah. that ain't right.

489
00:32:36.626 --> 00:32:38.879
Seems to me there's a road...

490
00:32:39.045 --> 00:32:41.798
Cow road that used to lead
all the way...

491
00:32:42.048 --> 00:32:45.302
Well. most of the way...
Er. that ain't right. either.

492
00:32:45.635 --> 00:32:52.475
- Hop in while you give it a think.
- Right. Delmar.

493
00:32:59.900 --> 00:33:02.652
Any of you boys know your way around
a Walther PPK?

494
00:33:02.903 --> 00:33:08.325
Well. we can't help.
I don't believe it's in Mississippi.

495
00:33:08.909 --> 00:33:12.245
Friend. some of your folding
money has come unstowed.

496
00:33:12.496 --> 00:33:15.248
Just stuff it
down that sack. will you?

497
00:33:15.582 --> 00:33:17.667
You boys aren't bad men. I take it?

498
00:33:17.834 --> 00:33:20.003
Well. it's funny you should ask.

499
00:33:20.253 --> 00:33:24.341
I was bad till yesterday.
but me and Pete here been saved.

500
00:33:24.591 --> 00:33:27.427
I'm Delmar.
and that there is Everett.

501
00:33:27.677 --> 00:33:31.515
George Nelson. It's a pleasure.

502
00:33:31.681 --> 00:33:35.852
Grab the tiller. will you. buddy?

503
00:33:40.190 --> 00:33:42.108
Hand me that chopper.

504
00:33:42.359 --> 00:33:45.445
Say. what line of work
you in. George?

505
00:33:47.697 --> 00:33:49.115
Come and get me. coppers!

506
00:33:49.366 --> 00:33:53.620
You flatfooted. lame-brained.
soft-ass sons of bitches!

507
00:33:53.787 --> 00:33:58.959
Ah ha! No one can catch me!
I'm George Nelson!

508
00:33:59.125 --> 00:34:03.380
I'm bigger than any John.
live or limp!

509
00:34:03.630 --> 00:34:08.552
I'm ten an' a half
feet tall!

510
00:34:09.553 --> 00:34:15.642
Cows. I hate cows worse than coppers!

511
00:34:16.476 --> 00:34:18.728
Oh. George... Not the livestock.

512
00:34:18.979 --> 00:34:24.234
Come on. you miserable salaried
sons of bitches! Come and get me!

513
00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:42.752
Come on. boys.
we're going for the record.

514
00:34:43.003 --> 00:34:44.504
Three banks in two hours!

515
00:34:52.012 --> 00:34:55.265
OK. folks. hold the applause
and drop your drawers!

516
00:34:55.515 --> 00:34:59.278
I'm George Nelson. and I'm here
to sack the city Itta Bena!

517
00:35:01.188 --> 00:35:03.440
He's a live wire. though. ain't he?

518
00:35:03.690 --> 00:35:06.776
All the money in a bag.
What are you lookin' at. grandpa?

519
00:35:07.027 --> 00:35:09.613
Pardon me. George.
you got a plan for escapin'?

520
00:35:09.946 --> 00:35:11.531
Sure. boys.

521
00:35:11.698 --> 00:35:13.783
Here's my plan. Ha ha!

522
00:35:14.117 --> 00:35:16.703
They ain't never seen
ordnance like this!

523
00:35:16.953 --> 00:35:18.788
Thank you. folks.

524
00:35:19.122 --> 00:35:24.127
And remember. Jesus saves.
but George Nelson withdraws!

525
00:35:24.461 --> 00:35:26.296
Go fix the auto voiture. Pete.

526
00:35:26.546 --> 00:35:29.549
Is it Babyface Nelson?

527
00:35:29.716 --> 00:35:32.802
Who said that?

528
00:35:32.969 --> 00:35:36.806
What ignorant. low-down. slanderisin'

529
00:35:37.015 --> 00:35:40.310
son of a bitch said that?!

530
00:35:40.477 --> 00:35:45.106
My name is George Nelson. get me?!

531
00:35:45.315 --> 00:35:48.485
She didn't mean nothin'
by it. George.

532
00:35:48.819 --> 00:35:51.822
George Nelson! Not Babyface!

533
00:35:52.155 --> 00:35:56.243
You remember!
And you tell your friends!

534
00:35:56.409 --> 00:35:58.829
I'm George Nelson.

535
00:35:59.162 --> 00:36:02.415
Born to raise hell.

536
00:36:19.266 --> 00:36:22.394
Well. that was some fun.
now. wasn't it. George?

537
00:36:22.686 --> 00:36:23.854
Yeah.

538
00:36:24.104 --> 00:36:26.857
Almost makes me wish
I hadn'ta been saved.

539
00:36:27.190 --> 00:36:28.441
Jacking up banks.

540
00:36:28.775 --> 00:36:32.195
I can see how a fella'd
derive a whole lot of pleasure

541
00:36:32.445 --> 00:36:34.364
and satisfaction out of it.

542
00:36:34.614 --> 00:36:38.869
