you're endowed with the gift of gab.

709
00:50:06.593 --> 00:50:10.430
I flatter myself such is the case.
In my line. it's plum necessary.

710
00:50:10.764 --> 00:50:14.100
The one thing you don't want...

711
00:50:14.267 --> 00:50:16.686
is air in the conversation.

712
00:50:17.020 --> 00:50:20.106
Again we agree.
What kind of work you do. Big Dan?

713
00:50:20.440 --> 00:50:22.859
Sales. Mr McGill. sales!
What do I sell?

714
00:50:23.026 --> 00:50:25.028
The truth. every blessed word of it.

715
00:50:25.195 --> 00:50:27.280
From Genesis down to Revelations.

716
00:50:27.614 --> 00:50:30.200
Yes. the word of God.
which. let me say.

717
00:50:30.450 --> 00:50:34.287
there's damn good money in
during these times of woe and want.

718
00:50:34.538 --> 00:50:38.708
People want answers. and Big Dan
sells the only book that's got 'em.

719
00:50:38.959 --> 00:50:43.547
And what do you do.
you and your. uh. tongue-tied friend?

720
00:50:43.880 --> 00:50:45.966
We...

721
00:50:46.216 --> 00:50:47.884
We're adventurers. sir.

722
00:50:48.051 --> 00:50:49.719
pursuing an opportunity.

723
00:50:49.970 --> 00:50:51.888
but we're open to others as well.

724
00:50:52.138 --> 00:50:55.141
I like you.
I'm gonna propose you a proposition.

725
00:50:55.475 --> 00:50:59.980
You cover my bill for now.
get your dinner wrapped picnic-style

726
00:51:00.147 --> 00:51:02.649
and we'll retire
to more private environs.

727
00:51:02.983 --> 00:51:05.569
where I'll reveal how to make
vast amounts of money

728
00:51:05.902 --> 00:51:07.737
in the service of God Almighty.

729
00:51:07.988 --> 00:51:11.741
Well. why not? I can use
some civilised conversation.

730
00:51:12.075 --> 00:51:14.244
Don't forget your shoe box. friend.

731
00:51:14.578 --> 00:51:17.747
Damn shame!
Goddam campaign is lagging!

732
00:51:18.081 --> 00:51:22.502
We need a shot in the arm.
Hear me. boys? In the goddam arm!

733
00:51:22.752 --> 00:51:27.090
Election held tomorrow. that
sumbitch Stokes would win in a walk!

734
00:51:27.340 --> 00:51:30.177
He's the reform candidate. Daddy.

735
00:51:30.427 --> 00:51:33.180
- Yeah?
- A lot of people like that reform.

736
00:51:33.430 --> 00:51:35.599
Maybe we should get us some.

737
00:51:35.849 --> 00:51:39.019
I'll reform you.
you soft-headed son of a bitch.

738
00:51:39.269 --> 00:51:41.938
How we gonna run reform?
We're the incumbent!

739
00:51:42.189 --> 00:51:45.275
Is that the best you can
come up with? Reform?!

740
00:51:45.525 --> 00:51:48.028
Weepin' Jesus on the cross.

741
00:51:48.361 --> 00:51:49.779
That's it!

742
00:51:50.030 --> 00:51:52.699
Start drafting my concession speech
right now.

743
00:51:52.949 --> 00:51:54.451
OK. Pappy.

744
00:51:54.701 --> 00:51:57.204
I'm just making a point.
you stupid son'bitch.

745
00:51:57.537 --> 00:52:00.874
- Give me back that hat!
- Pappy's just makin' a point.

746
00:52:01.041 --> 00:52:03.627
Shut up!

747
00:52:18.558 --> 00:52:22.562
Thank you for that fricassee.
I'm a man of large appetites.

748
00:52:22.729 --> 00:52:25.649
Even with lunch under my belt.
I was a mite peckish.

749
00:52:25.899 --> 00:52:26.900
Our pleasure.

750
00:52:27.234 --> 00:52:30.487
Thank you as well for
the conversational hiatus.

751
00:52:30.737 --> 00:52:33.824
I generally refrain
from speech during gustation.

752
00:52:33.990 --> 00:52:36.993
There are those who attempt
both at the same time.

753
00:52:37.327 --> 00:52:39.246
I find it coarse and vulgar.

754
00:52:39.412 --> 00:52:42.582
- Where were we?
- Making money in the Lord's service.

755
00:52:42.749 --> 00:52:46.169
Friend. when you do speak.
it's to the point and I salute you.

756
00:52:46.503 --> 00:52:48.255
Yes. Bible sales.

757
00:52:48.505 --> 00:52:52.759
The trade is not complicated.
There are two things to learn...

758
00:52:53.009 --> 00:52:54.678
One. find a wholesaler.

759
00:52:54.845 --> 00:52:56.429
the word of God in bulk. as it were.

760
00:52:56.763 --> 00:53:00.684
Two. recognise your customer.
Who are you dealing with?

761
00:53:00.934 --> 00:53:03.854
It's an exercise in psychology.
so to speak.

762
00:53:04.104 --> 00:53:11.778
And it is that which I propose
to give you a lesson in right now.

763
00:53:11.945 --> 00:53:15.615
I like to think I'm an astute
observer of the human scene. too.

764
00:53:15.782 --> 00:53:19.035
No doubt. brother.
I figured as much at the restaurant.

765
00:53:19.369 --> 00:53:24.457
That's why I invited you all out here
for this advanced tutorial.

766
00:53:24.791 --> 00:53:27.294
What's going on. Big Dan?

767
00:53:27.627 --> 00:53:30.547
It's all about the money. boys!
That's it!

768
00:53:30.797 --> 00:53:35.552
Gol... durned... money!

769
00:53:35.709 --> 00:53:36.666
I don't get it.

770
00:53:39.973 --> 00:53:43.643
I'll just take your show cards.

771
00:53:52.235 --> 00:53:55.739
And whatever you got in the hole.

772
00:53:58.992 --> 00:54:03.497
What the...
there ain't nothin' but a damn toad.

773
00:54:03.663 --> 00:54:09.586
No. you don't understand.
That's Pete.

774
00:54:12.005 --> 00:54:13.590
Pete.

775
00:54:13.757 --> 00:54:17.761
You know these give you warts?

776
00:54:25.185 --> 00:54:26.520
End of lesson.

777
00:54:29.189 --> 00:54:31.608
So long. boys. Hee hee!

778
00:54:31.858 --> 00:54:34.027
See you in the funny papers.

779
00:54:34.194 --> 00:54:38.532
Y'all seen the end of Big Dan Teague.

780
00:55:00.303 --> 00:55:05.642
Where are they? Talk.
you unreconstructed whelp of a whore!

781
00:55:05.809 --> 00:55:07.727
Where they headed?

782
00:55:07.894 --> 00:55:11.231
- Aah!
- Your screams won't save your flesh.

783
00:55:11.481 --> 00:55:13.984
- Aah!
- Only your tongue is. boy.

784
00:55:14.151 --> 00:55:16.736
- Where they headed?
- Aah!

785
00:55:28.748 --> 00:55:32.169
Whoa. hound.

786
00:55:38.425 --> 00:55:42.095
Sweet summer rain.

787
00:55:44.014 --> 00:55:47.350
Like God's own mercy.

788
00:55:47.517 --> 00:55:50.437
Your two friends
have abandoned you. Pete.

789
00:55:50.687 --> 00:55:53.857
They don't seem to care
about your hide.

790
00:55:59.029 --> 00:56:02.199
OK.

791
00:56:06.119 --> 00:56:09.623
Stairway to heaven. Pete.

792
00:56:11.708 --> 00:56:13.293
We shall all meet by and by.

793
00:56:13.627 --> 00:56:16.213
God damn it!

794
00:56:18.298 --> 00:56:19.883
God forgive me!

795
00:56:20.050 --> 00:56:23.220
Hold.

796
00:56:33.480 --> 00:56:37.150
Believe me. Delmar. he would
have wanted us to press on.

797
00:56:37.484 --> 00:56:41.571
Pete. rest his soul.
was one sourass son of a bitch

798
00:56:41.738 --> 00:56:44.908
and not given to pointless
sentimentality.

799
00:56:45.075 --> 00:56:48.078
It don't seem right getting
the treasure without him.

800
00:56:48.411 --> 00:56:51.414
Maybe it's for the best
he was squished.

801
00:56:51.748 --> 00:56:55.085
Why. he... was barely
a sentient being and...

802
00:56:55.335 --> 00:56:58.672
when we clean up and
get a little smellum in our hair.

803
00:56:58.839 --> 00:57:01.675
we're gonna feel
100% better about ourselves

804
00:57:02.008 --> 00:57:04.928
and about... life in general.

805
00:57:06.596 --> 00:57:10.183
Must be near Parchment Farm.

806
00:57:10.433 --> 00:57:12.102
Sorry sons of bitches.

807
00:57:12.435 --> 00:57:15.939
Seems like a year ago
we busted off the farm.

808
00:57:25.198 --> 00:57:26.867
Pete got a brother?

809
00:57:27.200 --> 00:57:31.204
Not that I'm aware.

810
00:57:32.622 --> 00:57:34.791
Heat must be getting to me.

811
00:57:43.466 --> 00:57:47.637
<i>Oh. the storm and its fury
raged today</i>

812
00:57:47.888 --> 00:57:52.475
<i>Crushing hope
that we cherished so dear</i>

813
00:57:52.726 --> 00:57:57.898
<i>The cloud and storm
will in time pass away</i>

814
00:57:58.064 --> 00:58:03.320
<i>And the sun again
will shine bright and clear</i>

815
00:58:03.570 --> 00:58:06.072
<i>Keep on the sunny side</i>

816
00:58:06.323 --> 00:58:08.575
<i>Always on the sunny side</i>

817
00:58:08.825 --> 00:58:13.079
<i>Keep on the sunny side of life</i>

818
00:58:13.413 --> 00:58:15.499
<i>It will help us every day</i>

819
00:58:15.665 --> 00:58:17.918
<i>It will brighten all the way</i>

820
00:58:18.084 --> 00:58:22.672
<i>If we'll keep on
the sunny side of life</i>

821
00:58:23.006 --> 00:58:27.761
<i>If we'll keep on
the sunny side of life</i>

822
00:58:29.763 --> 00:58:33.517
That was wonderful.
That sure was. Yes.

823
00:58:33.767 --> 00:58:36.853
Now. I know The Sunnysiders
would agree with me

824
00:58:37.103 --> 00:58:39.606
when I say that the great state
of Mississippi

825
00:58:39.856 --> 00:58:43.777
cannot afford four more years
of Pappy O'Daniel!

826
00:58:44.027 --> 00:58:46.780
Four more years of cronyism!

827
00:58:46.947 --> 00:58:49.866
Nepotism! Rascalism!

828
00:58:50.116 --> 00:58:53.954
Of service to the interests!

829
00:58:54.204 --> 00:58:57.290
Now. the choice. she's a clear 'un.

830
00:58:57.624 --> 00:59:01.127
Pappy O'Daniel.
slave of the interests...

831
00:59:01.378 --> 00:59:05.632
Homer Stokes. servant of
the little man. Right. little fella?

832
00:59:05.882 --> 00:59:07.133
He ain't lyin'!

833
00:59:07.300 --> 00:59:11.304
Ladies and gentlemen.
the little man has admonished me

834
00:59:11.471 --> 00:59:13.974
to grasp the broom of reform

835
00:59:14.224 --> 00:59:16.726
and sweep this state clean!

836
00:59:16.977 --> 00:59:20.063
It's gonna be.
"Back to the flour mill. Pappy"!

837
00:59:20.313 --> 00:59:22.649
The interests can handle themselves!

838
00:59:22.983 --> 00:59:26.820
Come Tuesday.
we're gonna sweep the rascals out!

839
00:59:28.905 --> 00:59:32.826
Clean government
is yours for the asking!

840
00:59:35.078 --> 00:59:37.747
Folks.
now the little Wharvey gals!

841
00:59:39.416 --> 00:59:43.587
Wharvey gals? Did he just say
"little Wharvey gals"?

842
00:59:43.837 --> 00:59:46.006
Come here. girls.

843
00:59:46.339 --> 00:59:48.091
What y'all gonna sing for us?

844
00:59:48.258 --> 00:59:50.260
"In the Highways".

845
00:59:50.594 --> 00:59:53.680
- God damn it all!
- You know them gals. Everett?

846
00:59:53.930 --> 00:59:55.182
<i>In the highways</i>

847
00:59:55.515 --> 00:59:57.017
<i>In the hedges</i>

848
00:59:57.350 --> 00:59:59.686
<i>In the highways</i>

849
00:59:59.853 --> 01:00:01.438
<i>In the hedges</i>

850
01:00:01.771 --> 01:00:04.024
<i>In the highways</i>

851
01:00:04.357 --> 01:00:06.109
<i>In the hedges</i>

852
01:00:06.359 --> 01:00:10.280
<i>I'll be somewhere
a-working for my Lord</i>

853
01:00:10.530 --> 01:00:12.449
<i>I'll be somewhere a-working</i>

854
01:00:12.699 --> 01:00:14.534
<i>I'll be somewhere a-working</i>

855
01:00:14.868 --> 01:00:18.705
<i>I'll be somewhere
a-working for my Lord</i>

856
01:00:19.039 --> 01:00:20.957
<i>I'll be somewhere a-working</i>

857
01:00:21.124 --> 01:00:23.126
<i>I'll be somewhere a-working</i>

858
01:00:23.460 --> 01:00:28.632
<i>I'll be somewhere
a-working for my Lord</i>

859
01:00:28.965 --> 01:00:30.717
Hey. girls!

860
01:00:30.967 --> 01:00:33.220
Daddy! Daddy!

861
01:00:35.639 --> 01:00:37.641
Daddy? He ain't our daddy.

862
01:00:37.807 --> 01:00:40.977
Hell I ain't.
What's this Wharvey? You're McGills.

863
01:00:41.228 --> 01:00:43.563
Not since you
got hit by that train.

864
01:00:43.730 --> 01:00:45.315
What? I wasn't hit by a train.

865
01:00:45.565 --> 01:00:49.486
- Mama says you was hit by a train.
- Blooey! Nothin' left.

866
01:00:49.820 --> 01:00:51.488
Just a grease spot on the L & N.

867
01:00:51.822 --> 01:00:54.407
Damn it. I wasn't hit by any train!

868
01:00:54.574 --> 01:00:56.159
Mama's got us back to Wharvey.

869
01:00:56.409 --> 01:00:59.496
- That's her maiden name.
- You got a maiden name. Daddy?

870
01:00:59.746 --> 01:01:01.832
Daddy don't have a maiden name...

871
01:01:01.998 --> 01:01:03.250
That's your misfortune.

872
01:01:03.500 --> 01:01:07.087
- And now mama's got a new beau.
- He's a suitor.

873
01:01:07.420 --> 01:01:09.089
Yeah. I heard about that.

874
01:01:09.339 --> 01:01:12.425
Mama says he's bona fide.

875
01:01:12.676 --> 01:01:15.178
Mmm. He give her a ring?

876
01:01:15.428 --> 01:01:16.680
Yes. sir. A big 'un.

877
01:01:16.930 --> 01:01:19.432
- Gold and gems.
- Mama checked it.

878
01:01:19.766 --> 01:01:21.601
- It's bona fide.
- He's a suitor.

879
01:01:21.852 --> 01:01:24.354
- What's his name?
- Vernon T Waldrip.

880
01:01:24.521 --> 01:01:26.273
- Uncle Vernon.
- Till tomorrow.

881
01:01:26.523 --> 01:01:27.858
Then he's Daddy.

882
01:01:28.108 --> 01:01:31.862
I am the only daddy you got.
I am the damn pater familias.

883
01:01:32.112 --> 01:01:35.615
But you ain't bona fide.

884
01:01:37.450 --> 01:01:38.952
Where's your mama?

885
01:01:39.202 --> 01:01:43.623
- At the five-and-dime.
- Buying nipples.

886
01:01:44.374 --> 01:01:46.710
<i>This way</i>

887
01:01:47.043 --> 01:01:51.131
<i>To take me home</i>

888
01:01:51.464 --> 01:01:56.052
<i>Kiss me more...</i>

889
01:01:59.139 --> 01:02:02.893
- Daddy!
- Hello. sugar! Ha ha!

890
01:02:03.143 --> 01:02:04.895
How's my little girl?

891
01:02:05.228 --> 01:02:06.730
Hi.

892
01:02:06.980 --> 01:02:09.483
- Who the hell's that?
- Starla Wharvey.

893
01:02:09.649 --> 01:02:11.568
Starla McGill. you mean.

894
01:02:11.902 --> 01:02:14.654
- You never told me.
- Cos you was hit by a train.

895
01:02:14.905 --> 01:02:17.407
Why are you telling our gals
I was hit by a train?

896
01:02:17.741 --> 01:02:20.243
Lots of respectable people
been hit by trains.

897
01:02:20.410 --> 01:02:22.329
Judge Hobby was hit by a train.

898
01:02:22.579 --> 01:02:24.247
What was I supposed to say.

899
01:02:24.498 --> 01:02:27.167
that you were jailed
and I divorced you from shame?

900
01:02:27.417 --> 01:02:31.922
I take your point. But it puts me in
an awkward spot vis á vis my progeny.

901
01:02:32.088 --> 01:02:38.678
Hello. Penny.
Is this gentleman bothering you?

902
01:02:39.429 --> 01:02:40.764
You Waldrip?

903
01:02:40.931 --> 01:02:44.184
Uh-huh. That's right.

904
01:02:56.696 --> 01:02:59.032
You been using my hair treatment?

905
01:02:59.199 --> 01:03:01.284
Your hair treatment?

906
01:03:01.535 --> 01:03:04.871
Excuse me.

907
01:03:06.623 --> 01:03:10.710
I got news. In case you hadn't
noticed. I wasn't hit by a train.

908
01:03:10.877 --> 01:03:13.296
and I have travelled
many a weary mile

909
01:03:13.630 --> 01:03:17.968
to be back with my wife
and my six daughters.

910
01:03:18.218 --> 01:03:21.304
- Seven. Daddy!
- That ain't your daddy. Alvanelle.

911
01:03:21.638 --> 01:03:22.973
Your daddy was hit by a train.

912
01:03:23.306 --> 01:03:24.641
Penny. you stop that!

913
01:03:24.975 --> 01:03:26.810
You stop it! Vernon here's got a job.

914
01:03:27.060 --> 01:03:30.313
Vernon's got prospects.
He's bona fide. What are you?

915
01:03:30.480 --> 01:03:32.065
I'll tell you what I am...

916
01:03:32.232 --> 01:03:35.485
I'm the pater familias.
and you can't marry him!

917
01:03:35.735 --> 01:03:37.654
I can. I am and I will. tomorrow.

918
01:03:37.988 --> 01:03:40.323
I gotta think about the Wharvey gals.

919
01:03:40.490 --> 01:03:42.659
They look to me for answers.

920
01:03:42.909 --> 01:03:45.162
Vernon can buy 'em
lessons on the clarinet.

921
01:03:45.412 --> 01:03:49.249
The only good thing you
ever did was get hit by that train!

922
01:03:49.499 --> 01:03:53.670
Well. you lying. unconstant succubus.

923
01:03:53.837 --> 01:03:57.924
Whoa. whoa!
You can't swear at my fiancée!

924
01:03:58.091 --> 01:04:03.013
Oh. yeah?
Well. you can't marry my wife!

925
01:04:24.618 --> 01:04:27.454
Who is that man?

926
01:04:27.621 --> 01:04:30.373
He's not my husband.

927
01:04:30.540 --> 01:04:36.379
Just a drifter. I guess.
Just some no-account drifter.

928
01:04:38.548 --> 01:04:42.552
And stay out of the Woolsworth!

929
01:04:47.057 --> 01:04:49.392
<i>I'll bet she does
imitations. too.</i>

930
01:04:49.726 --> 01:04:52.646
Deceitful. two-faced she-wolf.

931
01:04:52.896 --> 01:04:55.148
Never trust a female. Delmar.

932
01:04:55.398 --> 01:04:59.986
Remember that precept and your time
with me won't have been ill-spent.

933
01:05:00.237 --> 01:05:03.323
- OK. Everett.
- "Hit by a train".

934
01:05:03.490 --> 01:05:06.076
Truth means nothing to a woman.
Delmar.

935
01:05:06.326 --> 01:05:09.830
Triumph of the subjective.
You ever been with a woman?

936
01:05:10.163 --> 01:05:13.834
Well. I've...
I got to get the family farm back

937
01:05:14.167 --> 01:05:16.670
before I can start
thinking about that.

938
01:05:16.920 --> 01:05:18.839
That's right. If then.

939
01:05:19.005 --> 01:05:23.093
Believe me. a woman's the
most fiendish instrument of torture

940
01:05:23.343 --> 01:05:26.012
ever devised
to bedevil the days of man.

941
01:05:26.263 --> 01:05:29.015
Everett. I never figured you
for a pater familias.

942
01:05:29.349 --> 01:05:33.770
Ohh. yes. I have spread my seed.

943
01:05:33.937 --> 01:05:35.438
And look what it's...

944
01:05:37.357 --> 01:05:42.529
God damn it.
What the hell...?

945
01:06:40.504 --> 01:06:45.342
OK. boys.
Enjoy your picture show.

946
01:06:49.846 --> 01:06:53.433
<i>I have no money. honey</i>

947
01:06:53.600 --> 01:06:55.769
<i>How can I change?</i>

948
01:06:56.019 --> 01:07:01.525
Do... not... seek the treasure.

949
01:07:03.610 --> 01:07:09.783
Do not... seek the treasure.

950
01:07:10.116 --> 01:07:12.035
It's a bushwhack.

951
01:07:12.285 --> 01:07:15.205
They're fixin' an ambush.

952
01:07:15.372 --> 01:07:19.709
Do not seek the treasure.

953
01:07:22.879 --> 01:07:28.468
We... we thought you was...

954
01:07:28.718 --> 01:07:31.888
a toad.

955
01:07:34.558 --> 01:07:43.650
We... thought...
you... was... a... toad.

956
01:07:43.984 --> 01:07:48.155
Do not seek the treasure.

957
01:07:48.321 --> 01:07:52.742
Quiet there!
Watch the picture!

958
01:07:57.247 --> 01:07:58.665
I signed that bill.

959
01:07:58.999 --> 01:08:01.585
I signed a dozen agriculture bills.

960
01:08:01.835 --> 01:08:04.588
Everyone knows
I'm a friend of the farmer.

961
01:08:04.921 --> 01:08:07.757
What I gotta do.
start diddling livestock?

962
01:08:07.924 --> 01:08:11.178
We can't do that. Daddy.
We might offend our constituency.

963
01:08:11.428 --> 01:08:16.850
We ain't got a constituency!
Stokes got a constituency!

964
01:08:16.933 --> 01:08:19.102
Well. it's a well-run campaign.

965
01:08:19.352 --> 01:08:21.188
Midget and broom and whatnot.

966
01:08:21.438 --> 01:08:24.357
- Devil his due.
- Hell of an organisation.

967
01:08:24.524 --> 01:08:27.777
- Say. I got an idea.
- What's that. Junior?

968
01:08:28.111 --> 01:08:31.615
We can hire us a little fella
even smaller than Stokes's.

969
01:08:31.948 --> 01:08:34.117
You slump-shouldered sack of nuts!

970
01:08:34.367 --> 01:08:37.287
We'd look like a bunch
of johnny-come-latelys

971
01:08:37.454 --> 01:08:39.456
bringin' out our own midget.

972
01:08:39.789 --> 01:08:41.208
Don't matter how stumpy!

973
01:08:41.541 --> 01:08:46.213
That's the goddam problem. people
think Stokes has got fresh ideas.

974
01:08:46.546 --> 01:08:48.632
He's au courant
and we're the past!

975
01:08:48.798 --> 01:08:50.217
It's a problem of...

976
01:08:50.467 --> 01:08:52.052
- Perception.
- Right.

977
01:08:52.302 --> 01:08:55.222
- He's pulling our pants down.
- Gonna paddle some behind.

978
01:08:55.388 --> 01:08:57.557
Ain't gonna paddle it. Gonna kick it.

979
01:08:57.891 --> 01:09:01.478
- No. he's gonna paddle it.
- That's not a proper description.

980
01:09:01.728 --> 01:09:08.652
- That's how I'd characterise it.
- It's more of a kickin' situation.

981
01:09:22.415 --> 01:09:27.838
God... God forgive me.

982
01:09:28.171 --> 01:09:32.342
I could not gaze upon that fireshow.

983
01:09:32.592 --> 01:09:35.679
Pete.

984
01:09:35.846 --> 01:09:40.433
- Hold still!
- Can't... stand much longer.

985
01:09:40.684 --> 01:09:43.603
It was... it was
a mo-moment of weakness.

986
01:09:43.854 --> 01:09:45.856
Quit babblin'. we gotta skedaddle.

987
01:09:46.106 --> 01:09:48.191
That's all I got.

988
01:09:48.358 --> 01:09:50.026
They lured me out for a bathe

989
01:09:50.277 --> 01:09:53.697
and then they dunked me.
trussed me up like a hog.

990
01:09:54.030 --> 01:09:55.699
and turned me in for the bounty.

991
01:09:55.866 --> 01:09:58.618
Shoulda guessed it.
Typical womanly behaviour.

992
01:09:58.785 --> 01:10:01.288
We're lucky we left
before they came back.

993
01:10:01.538 --> 01:10:03.290
We didn't abandon you. Pete.

994
01:10:03.456 --> 01:10:05.709
We just thought you was a toad.

995
01:10:05.876 --> 01:10:08.295
No. they never did
turn me into a toad.

996
01:10:08.461 --> 01:10:11.298
Well. that was our mistake. then.

997
01:10:11.548 --> 01:10:16.553
We was beat up by a Bible salesman
and banished from Woolworths.

998
01:10:16.720 --> 01:10:19.723
Everett. was it the one branch
or all of them?

999
01:10:19.973 --> 01:10:22.809
Well. I ain't had it easy.
either. boys.

1000
01:10:22.976 --> 01:10:27.647
Frankly. uh. well. I...

1001
01:10:28.648 --> 01:10:31.151
I spilt my guts about the treasure.

1002
01:10:34.237 --> 01:10:38.408
I'm awful sorry
I betrayed you. fellas.

1003
01:10:38.742 --> 01:10:42.412
Must be my Hogwallop blood.

1004
01:10:43.246 --> 01:10:45.081
That's all right. Pete.

1005
01:10:45.332 --> 01:10:48.335
Awful white of you to take it
like that. Everett.

1006
01:10:48.668 --> 01:10:51.171
I feel wretched.

1007
01:10:51.338 --> 01:10:54.925
Spoiling your play for
a million dollar point two.

1008
01:10:55.175 --> 01:10:58.094
You should rip out my guts.

1009
01:10:58.428 --> 01:11:00.597
No. that's all right.

1010
01:11:02.599 --> 01:11:06.088
You boys are true friends!
Ohh!

1011
01:11:07.437 --> 01:11:10.106
You're my beaucoup friends.

1012
01:11:10.315 --> 01:11:14.277
Pete. I don't want you to
beat yourself up about this. eh?

1013
01:11:14.486 --> 01:11:22.118
I can't help it. but
that's a... a wonderful thing to say.

1014
01:11:23.870 --> 01:11:28.500
Yeah. Pete. uh...

1015
01:11:29.084 --> 01:11:33.380
Well. fact of the matter is...

1016
01:11:35.549 --> 01:11:37.217
Damn it...

1017
01:11:37.425 --> 01:11:40.804
There ain't no treasure.

1018
01:11:42.556 --> 01:11:44.808
Fact of the matter is
there never was.

1019
01:11:45.183 --> 01:11:46.810
But...

1020
01:11:47.144 --> 01:11:52.983
So where's all the money
from the armoured car job?

1021
01:11:53.066 --> 01:11:55.819
I never knocked over no armoured car.

1022
01:11:55.986 --> 01:11:59.406
I was sent up for
practising law without a license.

1023
01:11:59.656 --> 01:12:01.408
- But...
- I had to bust out.

1024
01:12:01.658 --> 01:12:05.287
My wife wrote me she was
getting married. I gotta stop it.

1025
01:12:07.080 --> 01:12:10.208
I had two weeks left
on my sentence.

1026
01:12:10.417 --> 01:12:12.502
I couldn't wait. wedding's tomorrow.

1027
01:12:12.669 --> 01:12:20.844
My added time for the escape.
I don't get out now till 19... 87.

1028
01:12:21.011 --> 01:12:22.762
I am sorry about that.

1029
01:12:23.096 --> 01:12:28.351
I'll be... 84 years old.

1030
01:12:28.602 --> 01:12:32.522
I guess they'll tack on
50 years for me. too.

1031
01:12:32.689 --> 01:12:37.110
Boys. we was chained together.
I had to tell you something.

1032
01:12:37.319 --> 01:12:42.532
Busting out alone
was not an option. I'm sorry.

1033
01:12:42.782 --> 01:12:46.369
84 years old.

1034
01:12:46.453 --> 01:12:49.831
Well. I'll only be 82.

1035
01:12:50.040 --> 01:12:52.792
You! You ruined my life!

1036
01:12:53.126 --> 01:12:55.712
You ruined my life!

1037
01:12:56.087 --> 01:12:58.048
I do apologise. Pete.

1038
01:12:58.381 --> 01:13:02.636
84 years old!
I'm becoming Papillon!

1039
01:13:02.928 --> 01:13:04.429
Delmar!

1040
01:13:08.642 --> 01:13:12.395
Now. boys. Boys.

1041
01:13:25.659 --> 01:13:32.749
<i>Eeny meeny meiny mo</i>

1042
01:14:10.537 --> 01:14:15.917
<i>Oh death</i>

1043
01:14:16.126 --> 01:14:21.214
<i>Whoa death</i>

1044
01:14:21.590 --> 01:14:26.470
<i>Won't you spare me over
till another year?</i>

1045
01:14:31.808 --> 01:14:34.686
<i>Well. I am death. none can excel</i>

1046
01:14:34.895 --> 01:14:39.316
<i>I'll open the door
to heaven or hell</i>

1047
01:14:39.483 --> 01:14:42.235
<i>Whoa. death. someone would pray</i>

1048
01:14:42.444 --> 01:14:47.199
<i>Could you wait to call me
another day?</i>

1049
01:14:47.407 --> 01:14:48.492
<i>Children pray...</i>

1050
01:14:48.742 --> 01:14:53.246
That's Tommy.
They got Tommy!

1051
01:14:54.331 --> 01:14:55.540
Noose.

1052
01:14:55.832 --> 01:14:58.752
<i>No longer prayin'...</i>

1053
01:14:59.127 --> 01:15:03.507
Sweet Jesus. we got to save him.

1054
01:15:03.673 --> 01:15:06.426
<i>I'll fix your feet
till you can't walk</i>

1055
01:15:06.593 --> 01:15:11.681
<i>I'll lock your jaw
till you can't talk</i>

1056
01:15:12.015 --> 01:15:15.268
<i>I'll close your eyes
so you can't see</i>

1057
01:15:15.435 --> 01:15:19.981
<i>- It's very dark...
- The colour guard.</i>

1058
01:15:20.357 --> 01:15:23.944
<i>Death. I come to take the soul</i>

1059
01:15:24.152 --> 01:15:28.698
<i>Leave the body and leave it cold</i>

1060
01:15:29.032 --> 01:15:32.494
<i>Oh death</i>

1061
01:15:32.786 --> 01:15:37.040
<i>Whoa death</i>

1062
01:15:37.249 --> 01:15:42.963
<i>Won't you spare me over
till another year?</i>

1063
01:15:44.798 --> 01:15:47.467
Brothers!

1064
01:15:47.801 --> 01:15:50.387
Oh. brothers!

1065
01:15:50.637 --> 01:15:58.562
We have all gathered here to preserve
our hallowed culture and heritage

1066
01:15:58.728 --> 01:16:04.818
from intrusion.
inclusion and dilution

1067
01:16:04.985 --> 01:16:07.821
of colour. of creed.

1068
01:16:08.155 --> 01:16:10.073
and of our old-time religion.

1069
01:16:10.323 --> 01:16:14.786
We aim to pull evil up by the root

1070
01:16:15.078 --> 01:16:21.042
before it chokes out the flower
of our culture and heritage.

1071
01:16:21.334 --> 01:16:25.130
And our women.
let's not forget those ladies. y'all.

1072
01:16:25.422 --> 01:16:28.258
looking to us for protection

1073
01:16:28.425 --> 01:16:33.263
from darkies.
from Jews. from papists.

1074
01:16:33.555 --> 01:16:36.266
and from all those smart-ass folks

1075
01:16:36.516 --> 01:16:39.269
say we come descended from monkeys.

1076
01:16:39.519 --> 01:16:42.606
- That's not my culture and heritage.
- Yes!

1077
01:16:42.939 --> 01:16:44.274
Is it yours?

1078
01:16:44.608 --> 01:16:46.693
No!

1079
01:16:46.943 --> 01:16:49.529
And so...

1080
01:16:49.696 --> 01:16:51.740
we gonna hang us a Negro.

1081
01:17:05.712 --> 01:17:10.717
I ain't never harmed you.
neither of you gentlemen.

1082
01:17:32.656 --> 01:17:36.576
I ain't never harmed nobody.

1083
01:17:38.328 --> 01:17:40.497
- Hey. Tommy.
- Huh?

1084
01:17:40.789 --> 01:17:42.582
Tommy. we come to rescue you.

1085
01:17:42.833 --> 01:17:44.918
That's mighty kind of you boys.

1086
01:17:45.168 --> 01:17:48.338
but I don't think nothing's
going to save me now.

1087
01:17:48.630 --> 01:17:52.509
The devil's come
to collect his due.

1088
01:17:52.801 --> 01:17:54.678
Don't be crazy. Tommy.

1089
01:17:54.886 --> 01:17:56.680
You don't wanna get hanged.

1090
01:17:56.972 --> 01:17:59.057
Well. naw. I don't reckon I do.

1091
01:17:59.266 --> 01:18:03.353
but that's the way it's working out.

1092
01:18:04.771 --> 01:18:06.439
Tommy. I got a plan.

1093
01:18:09.484 --> 01:18:12.028
No!

1094
01:18:16.241 --> 01:18:18.118
The colour guard is coloured.

1095
01:18:20.370 --> 01:18:23.790
Who made them the colour guard?

1096
01:18:25.375 --> 01:18:27.669
Run. boys!

1097
01:18:34.301 --> 01:18:35.385
No. no. son!

1098
01:18:38.388 --> 01:18:43.059
Can't let that flag
touch the ground!

1099
01:19:06.833 --> 01:19:08.752
Get your hands off me.

1100
01:19:09.002 --> 01:19:11.463
I can do this myself.
get away from me.

1101
01:19:11.755 --> 01:19:13.590
We should hire this man away.

1102
01:19:13.924 --> 01:19:16.218
- Good idea. Pappy.
- Hell of an idea.

1103
01:19:16.426 --> 01:19:20.180
- Can't beat 'em. join 'em.
- He'll join us. run our campaign.

1104
01:19:20.388 --> 01:19:24.476
- Power. wealth...
- No one says no to Pappy O'Daniel.

1105
01:19:24.768 --> 01:19:28.438
- Not with his blandishments.
- And powers of persuasion.

1106
01:19:28.647 --> 01:19:31.775
- What's his name again?
- The campaign manager?

1107
01:19:31.942 --> 01:19:33.777
- Waldrip.
- Vernon Waldrip.

1108
01:19:33.944 --> 01:19:37.531
- Vernon T Waldrip.
- Hmm.

1109
01:19:42.619 --> 01:19:44.830
It's invitation only.

1110
01:19:45.038 --> 01:19:47.958
- We'll have to sneak in.
- Hold on.

1111
01:19:48.124 --> 01:19:49.584
Wait a minute.

1112
01:19:49.793 --> 01:19:52.128
Who elected you
leader of this outfit?

1113
01:19:52.295 --> 01:19:56.466
Since we've been following your lead.
we got nothing but trouble.

1114
01:19:56.716 --> 01:19:59.469
I've gotten this close
to being strung up

1115
01:19:59.719 --> 01:20:02.722
and consumed in a fire
and whipped no end

1116
01:20:03.056 --> 01:20:04.808
and sunstroked and soggied.

1117
01:20:05.058 --> 01:20:06.476
And turned into a frog.

1118
01:20:06.726 --> 01:20:08.145
He wasn't turned into a frog.

1119
01:20:08.353 --> 01:20:12.649
Almost loved up. though.

1120
01:20:12.983 --> 01:20:15.902
So. you're against me now. too?

1121
01:20:16.153 --> 01:20:19.739
Is that how it is. boys?

1122
01:20:20.490 --> 01:20:27.038
The whole world and God Almighty...
now you?

1123
01:20:30.167 --> 01:20:31.918
I guess I deserve it.

1124
01:20:32.252 --> 01:20:35.755
Boys...

1125
01:20:36.089 --> 01:20:39.050
I know that I made
some tactical mistakes.

1126
01:20:39.259 --> 01:20:42.345
but if you just stick with me.
I got a plan.

1127
01:20:42.596 --> 01:20:44.931
Believe me. we can fix this thing.

1128
01:20:45.182 --> 01:20:47.684
I'll get my wife back. we'll leave.

1129
01:20:51.771 --> 01:20:54.691
Goddam disgrace!

1130
01:20:54.858 --> 01:20:57.444
Made a travesty
of the entire evening.

1131
01:20:57.694 --> 01:21:01.531
Ohh! What I wouldn't give
to get a hold of those agitators.

1132
01:21:01.781 --> 01:21:05.535
Whoever heard of such behaviour.
even amongst the coloured?

1133
01:21:05.785 --> 01:21:10.373
Mulattos. maybe. I suspect some
miscegenation in their heritage.

1134
01:21:10.624 --> 01:21:13.293
Using a Confederate flag
as a missile!

1135
01:21:13.627 --> 01:21:16.880
Crazy! No one's ever gonna believe
we're a real band.

1136
01:21:17.088 --> 01:21:19.966
I just gotta get close enough
to talk to her.

1137
01:21:20.217 --> 01:21:23.637
Comin' with us got more future than
marrying a guy called Waldrip.

1138
01:21:23.887 --> 01:21:26.389
I'm goddam bona fide.
I got the answers.

1139
01:21:26.640 --> 01:21:29.893
Everett. my beard itches.

1140
01:21:41.071 --> 01:21:45.659
"In the Jailhouse Now". fellas.
Neighbourhood of B.

1141
01:21:53.750 --> 01:21:57.838
Penny. Ahem.

1142
01:21:58.296 --> 01:22:03.051
- It's me.
- No.

1143
01:22:03.260 --> 01:22:04.553
Honey!

1144
01:22:04.845 --> 01:22:08.515
<i>I had a friend named Ramblin' Bob</i>

1145
01:22:08.723 --> 01:22:11.393
<i>He used to steal. gamble and rob</i>

1146
01:22:11.601 --> 01:22:16.857
<i>He thought he was
the smartest guy around</i>

1147
01:22:17.065 --> 01:22:18.358
<i>Well. I...</i>

1148
01:22:18.692 --> 01:22:23.363
We're leaving the state. pursuing
opportunities in another venue.

1149
01:22:23.613 --> 01:22:25.699
I got big plans.

1150
01:22:25.991 --> 01:22:28.702
Not minstrels.
I'm going to be a dentist.

1151
01:22:28.952 --> 01:22:33.540
I know this guy
who'll print me up a license.

1152
01:22:33.790 --> 01:22:36.918
<i>He's in the jailhouse now</i>

1153
01:22:37.127 --> 01:22:40.714
<i>Well. I told him once or twice</i>

1154
01:22:41.047 --> 01:22:45.051
<i>To stop playin' cards
and a-shootin' dice</i>

1155
01:22:45.260 --> 01:22:48.847
<i>He's in the jailhouse now</i>

1156
01:23:09.409 --> 01:23:11.328
<i>Bob liked to play his poker...</i>

1157
01:23:13.580 --> 01:23:15.749
Why. that is
an improper suggestion.

1158
01:23:16.041 --> 01:23:21.087
I can't switch sides
in the middle of a campaign...

1159
01:23:21.254 --> 01:23:24.841
especially to work for a man
who lacks moral fibre.

1160
01:23:25.008 --> 01:23:28.345
Moral fibre?
Why. you pasty-face son'bitch.

1161
01:23:28.553 --> 01:23:30.096
I invented moral fibre.

1162
01:23:30.430 --> 01:23:33.683
Pappy was displaying rectitude
when that egghead you work for

1163
01:23:34.017 --> 01:23:36.311
was still messin' his drawers!

1164
01:23:36.520 --> 01:23:39.272
- Psst! Honey.
- Go away.

1165
01:23:39.481 --> 01:23:41.942
I want to be what
you want me to be. honey.

1166
01:23:42.192 --> 01:23:45.028
I want you and the gals
to come with me.

1167
01:23:45.237 --> 01:23:50.033
<i>To stop playin' cards
and a-shootin' dice...</i>

1168
01:23:50.283 --> 01:23:53.703
What are you doing here. Pappy?

1169
01:23:53.870 --> 01:23:55.956
Someone let on we were
giving out liquor.

1170
01:23:56.164 --> 01:23:59.125
You'll laugh out the other side
of your face November.

1171
01:23:59.459 --> 01:24:01.127
Pappy'll be laughin' then.

1172
01:24:01.336 --> 01:24:05.048
- Not out the other side of his face.
- Just the regular side.

1173
01:24:19.062 --> 01:24:21.148
They're my daughters. too. Penny.

1174
01:24:21.398 --> 01:24:22.899
Ain't you ever heard of...?

1175
01:24:23.233 --> 01:24:25.485
<i>In constant sorrow</i>

1176
01:24:42.836 --> 01:24:46.673
<i>I am the man</i>

1177
01:24:47.007 --> 01:24:49.593
<i>Of constant sorrow</i>

1178
01:24:49.885 --> 01:24:52.262
<i>I've seen trouble...</i>

1179
01:24:52.471 --> 01:24:55.182
Hot damn!
It's the Soggy Bottom Boys!

1180
01:24:55.557 --> 01:25:00.103
<i>I bid farewell</i>

1181
01:25:00.312 --> 01:25:02.314
<i>To old Kentucky</i>

1182
01:25:02.522 --> 01:25:08.111
<i>The place where
I was born and raised</i>

1183
01:25:08.361 --> 01:25:10.864
<i>The place where he</i>

1184
01:25:11.198 --> 01:25:15.410
<i>Was born and raised...</i>

1185
01:25:34.805 --> 01:25:37.265
Holy moly! These boys are a hit!

1186
01:25:37.557 --> 01:25:39.935
But. Pappy. they's integrated.

1187
01:25:40.143 --> 01:25:42.479
Wait a minute.

1188
